==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mortling
<hw>Mort"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Morling</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An animal, as a sheep, dead of
disease or privation; a morling.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wool plucked from a dead sheep; morling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortmain</ent>⟦br⟧
